'''Leandro Despouy''' (April 4th, 1947. [[San Luis, Argentina|San Luis]], Argentina) is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[human rights]] lawyer. He was the [[United Nations]] Commission on Human Right's [[United Nations Special Rapporteur|Special Rapporteur]] on the Independence of Judges and Lawyers from August 2003 until end of July 2009 .{{ref|Cbs050623}}
Despouy was one of the five authors of a report on human rights abuses committed against the [[extrajudicial]] captives the [[United States]] detains at its naval base at [[Guantánamo Bay, Cuba|Guantanamo Bay]], [[Cuba]].
He played a significant role for the recognition of [[extreme poverty]] as a [[human rights]] issue within the United Nations system.
{{Wikisourcepar2|wikisource:The Despouy Report on Human Rights and Extreme Poverty|The Despouy Report on Human Rights and Extreme Poverty}}
From 2002 to 2016, Despouy was the president of the Auditoria General de la Nación of the Argentine Republic.
